The article is a press gaggle by Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton aboard Air Force One en route to New Orleans. Burton discusses various topics including the attacks in Lahore, the comprehensive strategy in Afghanistan and Pakistan, the President's trip to New Orleans, the Gulf Coast recovery efforts, meeting with dignitaries, the Zazi threat, the Pakistan aid bill, union leaders and the Senate Finance health care bill, and the Dow reaching over 10,000. Burton emphasizes the President's concern for civilian life, the ongoing assessment of the situation in Afghanistan and Pakistan, the President's commitment to the Gulf Coast recovery, the need for comprehensive strategy, and the President's focus on stabilizing the financial system and getting people back to work.